{"timestamp": "2025-12-03 15:39:19.817817", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting diagnosis report — SDN spine–leaf lab\\nOverview\\n- High-level conclusion: The SDN control plane (controller at 20.0.0.100) is unavailable. All OVS switches are configured to use that controller and are in fail_mode: secure. As a result, the OVS bridges are not forwarding host traffic (internal bridge interfaces are down / ovs-system down) and hosts in the same 10.0.0.0/24 subnets cannot reach each other. This is a control-plane outage causing data-plane isolation.\\n\\nEvidence collected (key findings)\\n1) Controller unreachable / not running\\n- OVS bridges are configured to use the controller at tcp:20.0.0.100:6633:\\n  - leaf_1 ovs-vsctl show: \"Controller \\'tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\\'\"\\n  - leaf_2 ovs-vsctl show: \"Controller \\'tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\\'\"\\n  - spine_1 ovs-vsctl show: \"Controller \\'tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\\'\"\\n- Active ping attempt to controller failed:\\n  - Tool error: \"Device `20.0.0.100` is not running.\" (controller unreachable / service not present)\\n\\n2) OVS bridges are present but bridge interfaces are down (ovs datapath not active)\\n- On leaf_1:\\n  - ovs-vsctl shows Bridge leaf_1 and controller set.\\n  - ip addr summary: ovs-system: state DOWN; leaf_1 (internal) interface: state DOWN\\n    - ip_addr excerpt: \"2: ovs-system: ... state DOWN\" and \"3: leaf_1: ... state DOWN\" while physical ports (eth0..eth12) are UP.\\n- On leaf_2:\\n  - ip addr excerpt: \"2: ovs-system: ... state DOWN\" and \"3: leaf_2: ... state DOWN\" while eth0..eth12 are UP.\\n- On spine_1:\\n  - ip addr excerpt: \"2: ovs-system: ... state DOWN\" and \"3: spine_1: ... state DOWN\" while physical management interface eth8 is UP with 20.0.0.1.\\n- Interpretation: The OVS kernel/system interface (ovs-system) and the internal bridge interface are DOWN despite physical interfaces showing UP. That indicates the OVS data-plane is not operating normally (likely because the controller connection is missing and fail-open is not enabled).\\n\\n3) Hosts are configured correctly but cannot ARP / communicate\\n- Host IPs:\\n  - host_1_1: 10.0.0.1/24\\n  - host_1_2: 10.0.0.2/24\\n  - host_2_1: 10.0.0.9/24\\n  - host_2_2: 10.0.0.10/24\\n- host_1_1 -> host_1_2 ping:\\n  - Output: \"From 10.0.0.1 icmp_seq=1 Destination Host Unreachable\" (4/4 lost)\\n- ARP / neighbor cache:\\n  - host_1_1 ip neigh: \"10.0.0.2 dev eth0 FAILED\"\\n- Interpretation: Layer 2 neighbor discovery (ARP) is failing across the leaf switch attachment; hosts send packets but receive no ARP replies — consistent with the leaf switch not forwarding frames.\\n\\n4) OVS behavior and configuration that explains blocking\\n- All bridges have fail_mode: secure (from ovs-vsctl show). With controller unreachable and fail_mode secure (no fail-open), OVS will not install or use forwarding rules and will block data-plane forwarding unless preinstalled local flows exist. The observed behavior (bridge internal interfaces down, no host-to-host connectivity) is consistent with that fail-mode + controller outage.\\n\\nAffected components (localization)\\n- Primary root cause device: SDN controller at 20.0.0.100 (controller process / VM not running or unreachable).\\n- Affected switches: spine_1, leaf_1, leaf_2 (OVS bridges all point to the dead/unreachable controller and are in fail_mode secure).\\n- Affected hosts: host_1_1, host_1_2, host_2_1, host_2_2 (hosts are isolated; ARP fails; intra-subnet ping fails).\\n- Management network: spine and leaf switches have management IPs (20.0.0.1, 20.0.0.5, 20.0.0.6) configured and show RX/TX counters, but they cannot contact the controller (or controller service not present).\\n\\nRelevant command outputs (selected excerpts)\\n- host_1_1 ping 10.0.0.2:\\n  - \"From 10.0.0.1 icmp_seq=1 Destination Host Unreachable\" — 4 transmitted, 0 received, 100% packet loss.\\n- host_1_1 ip neigh:\\n  - \"10.0.0.2 dev eth0 FAILED\"\\n- leaf_1 ovs-vsctl show:\\n  - Bridge leaf_1\\n    - Controller \"tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\"\\n    - fail_mode: secure\\n- leaf_1 ip addr:\\n  - \"2: ovs-system: <...> state DOWN\"\\n  - \"3: leaf_1: <...> state DOWN\"\\n  - but eth0..eth12 show UP; eth12 has inet 20.0.0.5/24\\n- spine_1 ip addr:\\n  - eth8: \"inet 20.0.0.1/24\" (management IP present)\\n  - \"2: ovs-system: ... state DOWN\"\\n  - \"3: spine_1: ... state DOWN\"\\n\\nRoot-cause analysis (concise)\\n- The immediate root cause of host connectivity loss is the controller being unavailable and the OVS bridges configured with fail_mode: secure. Without the controller the switches are not operating normal forwarding (internal bridge interfaces are down / ovs-system down), causing ARP and L2 forwarding to fail. Physical interfaces on switches are up and host IP settings are correct, so the problem is not physical link or host IP misconfiguration — it is the control-plane/controller availability and switch datapath state.\\n\\nSeverity and impact\\n- Severity: High. All inter-host traffic that depends on the SDN controller-installed forwarding rules is blocked. Hosts on the same leaf cannot ARP and thus cannot communicate.\\n- Scope: Affects all hosts attached to the OVS switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) in this topology.\\n\\nNotes / additional observations\\n- OVS version: 3.1.0 (from ovs-vsctl output).\\n- Management interfaces on switches have valid 20.0.0.x addresses and show packet counters, which means basic IP stack is up; however the controller endpoint itself is not accessible/running.\\n- get_reachability output (large) showed many reachability entries with unknown status — this tool run likely could not complete because the control-plane is down.\\n\\nNo remediation actions included (per instruction).\\nIf you want, I can next run targeted checks (controller process/status on 20.0.0.100 if accessible, or bring up OVS fail-open temporarily) — tell me which next diagnostic step you want., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='abad100c-58b1-4da1-ad92-62494b13e211'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5-mini", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
